15-JUL-2000: XFce 3.4.3
=======================
- xfwm
  * Fix race condition between application and colormapNotify event in 256 
    color mode
  * Partially fixed resize problem with XForms apps (the rest is not under WM control)

09-JUL-2000: XFce 3.4.3
=======================
- xfwm
  * Add config option "ForceFocus" to allow focus changes in focus follow mouse
    even if mouse pointer didn't move
  * Add config option "ClickRaise" to raise a window when a click occurs inside
    the application window even if focus follow mouse mode
  * Add a popup menu to Maximize button to allow vertical or horizontal 
     maximization
  * Fix problem causing Ted (Text Editor) to crash with a XSetInputFocus failed
    error
  * Fix problem with windows name and icon name causing xfwm to crash if no
    window name was provided by the applications.
  * Removed all "smart" or "clever" placements that were not clever at all and
    replaced them by a real dummy placement, smaller and faster.
  * Improve memory management (get rid of "free (0)" errors)
  * Improve speed
  * Various cleanup
- all
  * Add support for dmalloc (debug malloc)

26-JUN-2000: XFce 3.4.2
=======================
- xfwm
  * Fix problem with move icons

25-JUN-2000: XFce 3.4.1
=======================
- xfwm
  * Improve "fake" modifiers handling (Caps/Num/Scroll Lock)
  * Add Alt+Click move window (very handy)
  * Change default to raise window whenever a click occurs, even in focus follow
    mouse mode.
  * Add a small black frame around windows (cosmetics !)
  * Automatically change bitmap button color (black/white) depending on the 
    brightness of the current border color.
  * Double reparenting is back. MWM (tm) is designed like this, and I suspect 
    the removal of double reparenting to be the cause of some trouble with 
    Java (tm) and some other applications.
- xfce
  * Fixed memory leaks in libs/xpmext.c (function MyCreatePixmapFromXpmImage())
  * Remove polling
- all
  * Change module codes from M_* to XFCE_M_* 
  * Add new palette Helice
  * Add new default palette Helice
  * Add new palette (textured) "Bronze" by Thomas A. Gilchrist based on a 
    GNOME theme by Berin Loritsch.
- scripts
  * Fixed a bug preventing xcreensaver to be launched at startup
  * Update xfce_setup to reflect new directory structure (patch contributed by 
    Ken Sodemann, stufflehead@bigfoot.com)
- libs
  * Reduce redraw for clock widget
- other
  New fvwm2 configuration file contributed by Joerg Koenig
  (J.C.koenig@t-online.de)
  
04-JUN-2000: XFce 3.4.0
=======================
- xfwm
  * Improve focus-follow-mouse mode
  * Improve ButtonPress event handling
  * Remove double reparenting of windows.
  * Add bitmap buttons
  * Add a new function to set the number of visible buttons on the title bar
  * Fix some small memory leak in xfwm's configuration parsing functions.
  * Add new command line option -sync to run xfwm in synchronized mode
  * Add Ctrl+Meta+Left/Right to navigate between virtual desktops
    (Suggested by Jon_Winquist@raytheon.com)
  * Fix incompatibility between gnome-session and autoraise mode, causing the whole system
    to freeze.
- xfce 
  * Bug fixed : Adding an item to a popup menu without specifying an icon 
    could cause xfce to crash sometimes (bug reported by Victor Meghesan 
    <meghesan@usa.net>)
  * Reduce memory consumption (more than 500Kb less)
  * Add new palette "Standards" by Victor Meghesan <meghesan@usa.net>
  * Patch to handle a list of programs in config file by damien 
    <damien@mandrakesoft.com> (The idea is: instead of putting just one program,
    you can write a coma separated list of program, and the browser will take 
    the first one that matches)
- libs 
  * Update image redering functions to reflect latest gdk-pixbuf API changes.
  * Small code cleanup
  * Reduce memory leaks in xfcolor.c
- xfmountdev
  * Add a new script to be used as an action from xfce's toolbar.
    xfmountdev mounts a device on the specified mount point and launches xftree,
    and unmounts the device when xftree finishes.
- xftree
  * File extension is not case sensitive anymore
  * Add new extensions supported by default (xtree.reg file)
- xfterm
  * New implementation of the xfterm shell script by 
    Joakim Andreasson <karanne@flashback.net>
- all
  * Change system-wide configuration files location to be FHS compliant
    (Filesystem Hierarchy Standard). Contributed by Josip Rodin 
    <joy@cibalia.gkvk.hr>
  * New script by Victor Meghesan <meghesan@usa.net> to convert CDE(tm)
    style palettes to Xfce style.
  * Romanian localization by Daniel Statescu <Daniel.Statescu@bigfoot.com>
    Thanks Daniel !
  * Dutch localization by Myckel Habets <myckel@superweb.nl>
    Thanks Myckel !
    
